<p>I used linux <strong>efibootmgr</strong> command line tool to my UEFI boot menu. This post is all about what i have done to remove the menu entry from the grub bootloader.</p>

<p>you can install efibootmgr with following command.</p>

<p>Debian/Ubuntu/linux mint</p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>sudo apt install efibootmgr
</code></pre></div></div>
<p><br /></p>
<h3 id="see-current-entries">See Current Entries</h3>

<p>run following to see current entries or settings.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>efibootmgr
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>This shows the Bootorder of entries,boot number of each entry which is identified by hexadecimal number. (*) means that the boot entry is active.</p>

<div class="row mt-3">
    <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0">
        <figure>

  <picture>
    

    <!-- Fallback to the original file -->
    <img src="/assets/img/efibootmgr.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();" />

  </picture>

</figure>

    </div>
</div>

<p>You can see more information adding -v to show verbose information.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>efibootmgr -v
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><br /></p>
<h3 id="deleting-boot-entry">Deleting Boot Entry</h3>

<p>After deletion of linux disturbution on a hard disk (in my case it was rhel linux) i still had boot entry for the linux distro. To remove the boot entry for the distro you need to run the following.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>sudo efibootmgr -b &lt;bootnum&gt; -B
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>example:</p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>sudo efibootmgr -b 0001 -B
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>-b option specify the boot number. -B option delete respective boot number.</p>

<p> You can now see the boot entries by running <b>efibootmanager</b> or by rebooting the system.</p>

<p><br /></p>
